Task
Maximum element modulus
Write a function maxAbsValue that takes an array arr as an argument and returns the element that has the maximum absolute value (modulus). If the values ​​are equal, the first in the list is returned.
Use a loop in your solution. The use of the Math.max () method is not permitted.
Example:
• function maxAbsValue ([3, 7, -8, 1]) must return -8;
• function maxAbsValue ([- 11, 6, 12) must return 12;
• function maxAbsValue ([1, -2, 2]) must return -2;
• function maxAbsValue ([]) must return undefined


Solution
function maxAbsValue (arr) {
 let max = arr [0];
  if (arr.length === 0) return undefined;
  for (let i = 0; i <arr.length; i ++) {
    if (Math.abs (arr [i])> Math.abs (max))
      max = arr [i];
  }
  return max;
}
